<TITLE> Police finally confirm two bodies found </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 31 (bdnews24.com)Police finally confirmed that two bodies were recovered Saturday following worker riots at a Tongi garment factory, almost 12 hours after the deaths were first reported by the media. Scores were injured as police were forced to fire teargas and rubber bullets at a mob of angry workers, who said they found Nippon Garments factory at Ershad Nagar closed without notice in the morning. There were also widespread reports on the ground since morningfrom witnesses that included journalists, locals, bystanders as well as workersthat at least three people had been killed during the clashes between workers and police. Traffic on the Dhaka-Mymensingh highway was blocked for over four hours from 9am as the demonstrations spilled out onto the streets and workers vandalised over a dozen vehicles, setting two of them alight. Despite multiple witness accounts, however, police would not confirm any deaths until almost midnight. Tongi police chief Tapan Chandra Shaha told bdnews24.com around 11pm that two bodies were recovered; one was identified as Babul Sheikh, 30, the other could not be identified immediately. "They, of course, died in the clashes. But, they are not workers of Nippon Garments factory." He would not say from where their bodies had been recovered or how they died. "The cause of death will be revealed after post mortem," he said. bd
